ApplyCertificate.document: This API is used to apply for a free certificate.
ApplyCertificate.name: Applies for a free certificate

BatchDeleteCSR.document: This API is used to batch delete CSRs.
BatchDeleteCSR.name: Batch deletes CSRs

CancelCertificateOrder.document: This API is used to cancel a certificate order.
CancelCertificateOrder.name: Cancels a certificate order

CommitCertificateInformation.document: This API is used to submit a certificate order.
CommitCertificateInformation.name: Submits a certificate order

CreateCSR.document: This API is used to create a CSR.
CreateCSR.name: Creates a CSR

CreateCertificate.document: This API is used to purchase a certificate.
CreateCertificate.name: Purchases a certificate

CreateCertificateBindResourceSyncTask.document: This API is used to create an async task for querying the cloud resources associated with a certificate. If such a task already exists under the certificate ID, the ID of this task is returned as the result. The following types of cloud resources are supported: CLB, CDN, WAF, LIVE, VOD, DDOS, TKE, APIGATEWAY, TCB, and TEO (EDGEONE). You can query the result of this task using the `DescribeCertificateBindResourceTaskResult` API.
CreateCertificateBindResourceSyncTask.name: Creates an async task for querying cloud resources associated with a certificate

DeleteCertificate.document: This API is used to delete a certificate.
DeleteCertificate.name: Deletes a certificate

DescribeCSR.document: This API is used to query the details of a CSR.
DescribeCSR.name: Queries the details of a CSR

DescribeCSRSet.document: This API is used to query the CSR list.
DescribeCSRSet.name: Queries the CSR list

DescribeCertificate.document: This API is used to get certificate information.
DescribeCertificate.name: Gets certificate information

DescribeCertificateBindResourceTaskDetai.document: This API is used to query the result of an async task created with `CreateCertificateBindResourceSyncTask` to query cloud resources associated with a certificate. The following types of cloud resources are supported: CLB, CDN, WAF, LIVE, VOD, DDOS, TKE, APIGATEWAY, TCB, and TEO (EDGEONE).
DescribeCertificateBindResourceTaskDetai.name: Queries the result of a task querying cloud resources associated with a certificate (details of associated cloud resources are returned)

DescribeCertificateBindResourceTaskResul.document: This API is used to query the result of an async task created with `CreateCertificateBindResourceSyncTask` to query cloud resources associated with a certificate. The following types of cloud resources are supported: CLB, CDN, WAF, LIVE, VOD, DDOS, TKE, APIGATEWAY, TCB, and TEO (EDGEONE).
DescribeCertificateBindResourceTaskResul.name: Queries the result of a task querying cloud resources associated with a certificate (only the total number of associated cloud resources is returned)

DescribeCertificateDetail.document: This API is used to get certificate details.
DescribeCertificateDetail.name: Gets certificate details

DescribeCertificateOperateLogs.document: This API is used to get certificate operation logs in the current account.
DescribeCertificateOperateLogs.name: Gets certificate operation logs

DescribeCertificates.document: This API is used to get the certificate list.
DescribeCertificates.name: Gets the certificate list

DownloadCertificate.document: This API is used to download a certificate.
DownloadCertificate.name: Downloads a certificate

ModifyCSR.document: This API is used to modify the information of a CSR.
ModifyCSR.name: Modifies the information of a CSR

ModifyCertificateAlias.document: This API is used to modify a certificate alias by passing in the certificate ID and new alias.
ModifyCertificateAlias.name: Modifies a certificate alias

ModifyCertificateProject.document: This API is used to modify the projects of multiple certificates.
ModifyCertificateProject.name: Modifies the projects of multiple certificates

ReplaceCertificate.document: This API is used to reissue a certificate. Note that if you have applied for a free certificate, only an RSA-2048 certificate will be reissued, and the certificate can be reissued only once.
ReplaceCertificate.name: Reissues a certificate

SubmitCertificateInformation.document: This API is used to submit certificate information.
SubmitCertificateInformation.name: Submits certificate information

UploadCertificate.document: This API is used to upload a certificate.
UploadCertificate.name: Uploads a certificate

UploadConfirmLetter.document: This API is used to upload the confirmation letter for a certificate.
UploadConfirmLetter.name: Uploads the confirmation letter for a certificate
